The paper introduces a new type of gated RNN architecture and evaluates its performance on language modeling tasks. This suggests that the paper could be relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computer vision (cs.CV). However, given the focus on language modeling, cs.LG and cs.CL are the most likely categories, followed by cs.NE, cs.AI, and cs.CV.
